 704:     """Fast, re-entrant locking.


 705: 


 706:     Under uncongested conditions, the lock is never acquired but only


 707:     counted.  Only when a second thread comes in and notices that the


 708:     lock is needed, it acquires the lock and notifies the first thread


 709:     to release it when it's done.  This is all made possible by the


 710:     wonderful GIL.


 711:     """


 712:     cdef pythread.PyThread_type_lock _real_lock


 713:     cdef long _owner            # ID of thread owning the lock


 714:     cdef int _count             # re-entry count


 715:     cdef int _pending_requests  # number of pending requests for real lock


 716:     cdef bint _is_locked        # whether the real lock is acquired
